    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UL SCH Rel10 packing function behavior\n\n### Summary\nWhen calling `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel10_value()` the behavior is not what is expected. Investigation revealed two main issues:\n\n1. A critical bug in the corresponding unpacking function where a single `&` was used instead of `&&` causing incorrect logical evaluation\n2. Missing NULL pointer validation in packing functions that could lead to crashes\n\nThe fix addresses these issues by correcting the logical operator in the unpacking function and adding proper input validation to all UL SCH packing functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: \n  - Fixed bitwise AND to logical AND in `unpack_ul_config_ulsch_pdu_rel10_value`\n  - Added NULL pointer checks to `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel8_value`\n  - Added NULL pointer checks to `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel10_value` \n  - Added NULL pointer checks to `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel11_value`\n  - Added NULL pointer checks to `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel13_value`\n\n"
}